2. The brake assembly of claim 1 wherein said switch further comprises: 
a pressure sensor port for receiving said pressure signal; 
an input port for receiving said brake signal; 
a brake cylinder port for providing said brake signal to said brake cylinder; and 
a spring responsive to said pressure signal to permit said switch to connect or disconnect said input port with said brake cylinder port.

7. A brake system for a vehicle having an air spring, comprising: 
a control valve providing a brake signal; 
an air spring providing a pressure signal; 
a brake cylinder; 
a proportioning valve connected to and responsive to said brake signal to provide a proportioned brake signal to said brake cylinder; and 
a switch responsive to said pressure signal from said air spring to selectively connect and disconnect said brake signal to said brake cylinder.

9. The brake system of claim 8 wherein said switch further comprises: 
a pressure sensor port for receiving said pressure signal; 
an input port for receiving said brake signal; 
a brake cylinder port for sending said brake signal to said brake cylinder; and 
a spring responsive to said pressure signal to permit said switch to connect or disconnect said input port with said brake cylinder port.
